column1: 275248;instagram;2018-10-24 16:33:00;FALSE;"i caught a lot of heat a couple years ago for a post expressing my opinion about the woman’s march. during that time i was being tormented by male and female staff and management for coming forward about sexual harassment. i continued to fight for what i believed i
column2: and every other woman working for doc deserved in a working environment. i didn’t stand in the street with a sign. i didn’t march in protest. i didn’t victimize myself and try to get someone else to fix the problem. i put on my big girl pants and i fought like hell for two years. i hope this article reaches even one woman struggling with sexual harassment in the workplace and gives her the strength to come forward and fight a system that is so badly broken. i’m not a raging feminist with any hidden agenda. i’m just a single mother who fought my ass off for justice against people who destroyed years of my life for simply trying to do the right thing. i wish at the end of this i could say i made a difference but the sad truth is the problem is so widespread and systemic it’s going to take a lot more voices coming forward and fighting

column1: please share this post and get the word out that it’s okay to come forward in a real way. you have options. you are not stuck. you don’t deserve to be sexually harassed and abused. #metoo #greylivesmatter #thingreyline #womenhelpingwomen #womenincorrections #womeninlawenforcement #vermont #burlingtonfreepress #corrections #doc";;en;#MeToo.

column1: inspired me to and it is very personal. i thought a lot about posting this or not - especially because my patients (i work as a psychologist) could see this and it could damage my reputation and integrity. but my mentor always say: be authentic. and truth is psychologists are also just humans and a good outcome from my experiences is my empathy. and it helps no one to shut your mouth. not you and not people who experienced similar.
i think i showed here on instagram a lot that i'm in a relationship that makes me very very happy ❤
but before this relationship and before my time as a happy single
column2: i was in an abusive relationship with a man that did a lot of emotional damage to me. that doesn't mean this man was a bad person. he didn't plan to hurt me but in fact he did. and it made me loose trust in both - myself and other people.

column1: this is what the artwork shows. i know i wrote it was about seeing beloved people suffer but in fact it was about my own suffering. it shows how i was drowning while i was still holding on to this relationship and to this person. but it took me so long to realize that. and i felt so damaged and i tried to hide that. but i realized that this isn't the right way. there is nothing wrong with me and never has been.
what can i say: i still struggle a bit with trust but as soon as i realized what was going on.. i started to build myself up again
column2: i started to take care of myself again
column3: i started to love myself again and i understood that everyone is worth to be treated with respect. and i think it is important to talk about these things because i know there are a lot of women with similar experience. just know that you are not alone and that everyone is worth to be loved. ❤ and if anyone makes you feel wrong or weak or if it just doesn't feel right

column1: you are worth everything you ever dreamed of! ❤❤❤

column1: هنوز خبر جایزه‌ی نوبل صلح نادیه مراد تازه است و «می تو» هم به تازگی یک‌ساله شد. با جنبش «می تو» کاملا همدل نبودم. به ویژه در اوایل کارش. نقدهایی هم بر اعطای آن جایزه خواندم. اما ارزش و اهمیت هردو برایم، بیش از هرچیز، در «نترسیدن» است. نترسیدن از گفتن. شکستن سکوت. همه‌ی دخترها تجربه‌ی تعرض جنسی در کودکی و نوجوانی و بعدتر، از آشنا و غریبه، را دارند. گاهی حتی نمی‌دانیم این‌ها تعرض‌اند. گاهی انتخاب می‌کنیم که سکوت کنیم. از شرم. از ترس. کاری که من هم کرده‌ام. در برابر آشنایان. در برابر جوانکی که با زور، در روز روشن در خیابان، در ۱۹ سالگی‌ام، خواست «من» را و نه اموالم را بدزدد، و از ترس انتقام و مزخرفاتی چنین به پلیس شکایت نبردم. حتی در برابرِ مثلا کیوریتور-منتقد یا هر کوفت دیگری که به بهانه‌ی حرف‌زدن به اتاقش دعوتم کرد و در بدو ورود، بی درنگ، پوست انداخت و چونان حیوانی وحشی غرید، و من؟ تنها هنرم گریختن از مهلکه. و من؟ سکوت. یا نقاش پیری که پیرانه سرش هوس جوانی (با مصاحبه‌گرش) به سر افتاد! و من؟ همان، و همان...
شما چندین بار، و هربار در چه موردی سکوت کرده‌اید؟

چرا؟ شاید چون اغلب نوک پیکان برگشته به زن. به آن «کرم از خود درخت‌ است» ها! نمی‌دانم. ولی این را می‌دانم که اگر این‌جا ها سکوت کرده‌ایم، هرگز نمی‌فهمیم تصمیم به ایستادن در برابر «داعش» و یحتمل ترسی مداوم در برابر جسارتی چنان یعنی چه...

";❎ هنوز خبر جایزه‌ی نوبل صلح نادیه مراد تازه است و « می تو » هم به تازگی یک‌ساله شد . با جنبش « می تو » کاملا همدل نبودم . به ویژه در اوایل کارش . نقدهایی هم بر اعطای آن جایزه خواندم . اما ارزش و اهمیت هردو برایم، بیش از هرچیز، در « نترسیدن » است . نترسیدن از گفتن . شکستن سکوت . همه‌ی دخترها تجربه‌ی تعرض جنسی در کودکی و نوجوانی و بعدتر، از آشنا و غریبه، را دارند . گاهی حتی نمی‌دانیم این‌ها تعرض‌اند . گاهی انتخاب می‌کنیم که سکوت کنیم . از شرم . از ترس . کاری که من هم کرده‌ام . در برابر آشنایان . در برابر جوانکی که با زور، در روز روشن در خیابان، در ۱۹ سالگی‌ام، خواست « من » را و نه اموالم را بدزدد، و از ترس انتقام و مزخرفاتی چنین به پلیس شکایت نبردم . حتی در برابرِ مثلا کیوریتور-منتقد یا هر کوفت دیگری که به بهانه‌ی حرف‌زدن به اتاقش دعوتم کرد و در بدو ورود، بی درنگ، پوست انداخت و چونان حیوانی وحشی غرید، و من؟ تنها هنرم گریختن از مهلکه . و من؟ سکوت . یا نقاش پیری که پیرانه سرش هوس جوانی ( با مصاحبه‌گرش ) به سر افتاد ! و من؟ همان، و همان ... شما چندین بار، و هربار در چه موردی سکوت کرده‌اید؟ چرا؟ شاید چون اغلب نوک پیکان برگشته به زن . به آن « کرم از خود درخت‌ است » ها ! نمی‌دانم . ولی این را می‌دانم که اگر این‌جا ها سکوت کرده‌ایم، هرگز نمی‌فهمیم تصمیم به ایستادن در برابر « داعش » و یحتمل ترسی مداوم در برابر جسارتی چنان یعنی چه ... ;[('❎'

column1: 275366;instagram;2018-10-24 15:31:54;TRUE;;"#repostsave @kailayu with @repostsaveapp ・・・ ok this has nothing to do with this photo but.....just needed to speak out in light of all the recent #metoo controversies. i had a very traumatic sexual experience that occured about 20 years ago. it included a good amount of public shaming. it's not a situation that i've ever wanted to revisit but i think it's so important that women are not ashamed by situations in which they have been victimized in the past and instead use the healing from these experiences to become more powerful women. i also want to write it as a cautionary tale so that it may help younger women from getting into the same extremely dangerous situations. this is a work in progress and so i will keep you all posted on when the piece is completed. but i want to encourage all women to speak out about their experiences more so that any shame or stigma is removed from these ordeals.

column1: 275411;instagram;2018-10-24 14:30:23;FALSE;"yoko ono’s wish tree for peace is an iconic work that she has created in cities and spaces around the world since the 1990s. the piece encourages viewers to interact with her creative practice and buddhist tradition by leaving their wishes tied to the branches of a tree in public space-- their act becoming a part of the creation of the artwork as both a performative participatory gesture and later as a document in ono’s imagine peace tower.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

column2: but it’s still painful to recall. “for a long time
column3: i tortured myself by blaming myself for everything
column4: ” she tells time in seoul. seo alleges she was repeatedly groped at a funeral by a senior male colleague
column5: while the country’s justice minister sat nearby
column6: in 2010. seo reported the incident to her managers shortly after
column7: but was subjected to performance audits that she describes as unfair
column8: and assigned to a lower level branch outside seoul—a move she says did not match her strong track record at work. last fall
column9: seo watched as #metoo took off. she began to grasp how widespread sexual harassment and assault were. seo added her voice to the rising global chorus in january
column10: sharing her experience in an open letter on her workplace intranet and signing it with #metoo. within a few hours of posting

column13: seo spoke on one of south korea’s most influential news programs. her words resonated: she is widely credited with kick-starting south korea’s version of the movement. women’s rights activists and survivors across asia have seen the global reckoning confronting sexual harassment
column14: assault and abuse as a chance to shape their own national conversations about gender #inequality

column1: this month is black history month in the uk and it is upsetting to see the ryanair racism scandal that has been allowed to happen on board a flight.
if that situation happened on board one of my flights
column2: i would have asked for the removal of the disruptive male passenger.
in london my home city i was subjected to racism too.  i was approached by an aggressive middle aged skin head who walked up to me
column3: staring. he looked me up and down and asked “and where are you from?” exclaiming to me that he is pure english and born in streatham
column4: he maintained his aggressive behaviour and eye contact before a staff member distracted him. he hovered outside the shop for a while possibly waiting for me. i’ve not felt so threatened in a long time and my gut feeling thought my muay thai boxing skills may need to come out.

column1: racism is not ok. it should be a thing of the past by now!
we are all the same: flesh and bone. we all have the same needs and we all should be allowed to live peacefully no matter who we are.
the only thing that should be separated by colour is laundry!

column4: he maintained his aggressive behaviour and eye contact before a staff member distracted him. he hovered outside the shop for a while possibly waiting for me. i’ve not felt so threatened in a long time and my gut feeling thought my muay thai boxing skills may need to come out.

the only thing that should be separated by colour is laundry!

column1: 275472;instagram;2018-10-24 14:19:24;FALSE;"생각해보면 여중여고를 다니는 동안 이상한 일들이 참 많았다.
나와 같은 학교를 나왔다면 모두 알겠지만
모든 남자는 룸사롱에 간다며 너네 아빠도 마찬가지라던 과학선생도 있었고
넌 다리가 예쁘니까 사장님이 예뻐할거라던 역사선생
나도 남자니까 다리 좀 오무리고 있으라던 진로선생
다시 생각해보면 숨막히고 거지같았던 일들을 그때는 어떻게 그런식으로 넘어갔는지 모르겠다.
지금이라도 이런일을 겪고 있는 학생들이 더 크게 당당하게 목소리를 낼 수 있게 힘쓰고싶다.
이 글을 보고 저 선생들이 누군지 알고 글을 쓰고싶다면 그냥 써줬으면 좋겠다.

column1: 275476;instagram;2018-10-24 11:47:27;FALSE;we get a lot of questions like “how do tiny homes work in the winter?”. it’s pretty simple!  we design each home so the plumbing never goes in an exterior wall and is always interior to the heated space.  that means you just have to worry about how your water gets into and out of your tiny home.  mobile homes have been operating this way for many years.  you add insulated skirting around the bottom to keep underneath above freezing.  there are several resources online for tiny living in cold climates - check them out! #winterscoming #mainewinter #tinyliving #liveauthentic #tinyhomes #simplicity #thow #mainetinyhouse #gottiny #tinyhomesofmaine #smartdesign #thoughtful #plan #downsize #retirement #tinyhouse #homeiswhereyouparkit #lesshousemorehome #qualitybuilt;;en;#winterscoming

هل فعلاً #نانا_باتيكار خارج فيلم #هوسفول_4؟ ابن الممثل ، ""لا يمكن التعليق"". المخرج فرهاد تم اغلاق الخط . .

للاسف الغموض الذي يكتسح حول خروج نانا بتيكار من هوسفول 4. كثرت التقارير بشكل كثيف و منذ المساء ، حيث أن نانا قام بـ تصوير أجزاء في جايسالمير هي جزء لا يتجزأ ولن يتم حذفها. من ناحية أخرى ، لم يقوم منتج الفيلم ساجد نياديادوالا ولا مخرج الفيلم فرهاد بأي تصريح رسمياً. اتصلنا على ابن نانا مالهار. و لم يرد على مكالماتنا ، ولكن تم ارسال رساله له عن وضع والده في هوسفول 4 ، رد علينا بـ رسالة ""آسفة ، لا يمكنني التعليق الآن على أي شخص. عندما أتمكن من ذلك ، سأعلمكم بالتأكيد"". من ناحية أخرى ، تصرف فرهاد بطريقة غريبة. اتصل بـ  مخرج هوسفول 4 في السابعة من صباح اليوم التالي ، لكنه رفض استقبال مكالماتنا قبل وبعد ذلك. عندما طلبنه ، تم رد لكن كان الصمت من الطرف الآخر حتى اغلق من نفسه في النهاية.

لا ينبغي أن ننسى أن نانا قد تصرفت بشكل غريب على التهم التي فرضتها تانوشري دوتا ، التي وضعت في حملة #metoo . الصحفيين الذين كانوا مستعدين له بقائمة طويلة من الأسئلة في اليوم الثاني ، ومع ذلك قام بإلغاء مؤتمره الصحفي الذي أعلنه هو بنفسه بالكثير من بلبله. بعد عودته من جايسالمير بعد الانتهاء من جدول تصوير هوسفول 4 ، لم نشاهد نانا على أي حال.
تتوقعون . ان هوسفول 4 سيتأخر بتصوير ؟ او  أن فرهاد وناديادوالا ما زالا يحاولان حل موضوع بتبديل مثلا ؟
‏नाना पाटेकर वास्तव में हाउसफुल 4 से बाहर है? अभिनेता का बेटा कहता है

هل فعلاً #نانا_باتيكار خارج فيلم #هوسفول_4؟ ابن الممثل ، ""لا يمكن التعليق"". المخرج فرهاد تم اغلاق الخط . .

للاسف الغموض الذي يكتسح حول خروج نانا بتيكار من هوسفول 4. كثرت التقارير بشكل كثيف و منذ المساء ، حيث أن نانا قام بـ تصوير أجزاء في جايسالمير هي جزء لا يتجزأ ولن يتم حذفها. من ناحية أخرى ، لم يقوم منتج الفيلم ساجد نياديادوالا ولا مخرج الفيلم فرهاد بأي تصريح رسمياً. اتصلنا على ابن نانا مالهار. و لم يرد على مكالماتنا ، ولكن تم ارسال رساله له عن وضع والده في هوسفول 4 ، رد علينا بـ رسالة ""آسفة ، لا يمكنني التعليق الآن على أي شخص. عندما أتمكن من ذلك ، سأعلمكم بالتأكيد"". من ناحية أخرى ، تصرف فرهاد بطريقة غريبة. اتصل بـ  مخرج هوسفول 4 في السابعة من صباح اليوم التالي ، لكنه رفض استقبال مكالماتنا قبل وبعد ذلك. عندما طلبنه ، تم رد لكن كان الصمت من الطرف الآخر حتى اغلق من نفسه في النهاية.

لا ينبغي أن ننسى أن نانا قد تصرفت بشكل غريب على التهم التي فرضتها تانوشري دوتا ، التي وضعت في حملة #metoo . الصحفيين الذين كانوا مستعدين له بقائمة طويلة من الأسئلة في اليوم الثاني ، ومع ذلك قام بإلغاء مؤتمره الصحفي الذي أعلنه هو بنفسه بالكثير من بلبله. بعد عودته من جايسالمير بعد الانتهاء من جدول تصوير هوسفول 4 ، لم نشاهد نانا على أي حال.
تتوقعون . ان هوسفول 4 سيتأخر بتصوير ؟ او  أن فرهاد وناديادوالا ما زالا يحاولان حل موضوع بتبديل مثلا ؟

‏ ";1. . . . هل فعلاً خارج فيلم ابن الممثل ، `` لا يمكن التعليق '' . المخرج فرهاد تم اغلاق الخط . . . . للاسف الغموض الذي يكتسح حول خروج نانا بتيكار من هوسفول 4 . كثرت التقارير بشكل كثيف و منذ المساء ، حيث أن نانا قام بـ تصوير أجزاء في جايسالمير هي جزء لا يتجزأ ولن يتم حذفها . من ناحية أخرى ، لم يقوم منتج الفيلم ساجد نياديادوالا ولا مخرج الفيلم فرهاد بأي تصريح رسمياً . اتصلنا على ابن نانا مالهار . و لم يرد على مكالماتنا ، ولكن تم ارسال رساله له عن وضع والده في هوسفول 4 ، رد علينا بـ رسالة `` آسفة ، لا يمكنني التعليق الآن على أي شخص . عندما أتمكن من ذلك ، سأعلمكم بالتأكيد '' . من ناحية أخرى ، تصرف فرهاد بطريقة غريبة . اتصل بـ مخرج هوسفول 4 في السابعة من صباح اليوم التالي ، لكنه رفض استقبال مكالماتنا قبل وبعد ذلك . عندما طلبنه ، تم رد لكن كان الصمت من الطرف الآخر حتى اغلق من نفسه في النهاية . لا ينبغي أن ننسى أن نانا قد تصرفت بشكل غريب على التهم التي فرضتها تانوشري دوتا ، التي وضعت في حملة . الصحفيين الذين كانوا مستعدين له بقائمة طويلة من الأسئلة في اليوم الثاني ، ومع ذلك قام بإلغاء مؤتمره الصحفي الذي أعلنه هو بنفسه بالكثير من بلبله . بعد عودته من جايسالمير بعد الانتهاء من جدول تصوير هوسفول 4 ، لم نشاهد نانا على أي حال . تتوقعون . ان هوسفول 4 سيتأخر بتصوير ؟ او أن فرهاد وناديادوالا ما زالا يحاولان حل موضوع بتبديل مثلا ؟ . . . . . . . . . ‏नाना पाटेकर वास्तव में हाउसफुल 4 से बाहर है ? अभिनेता का बेटा कहता है

column8: to exist. i have never had to see the world through the black experience. though as a liberal i was sure that i had. there was an episode of my old show the sarah silverman show where i could not see past the scope of my liberal white lens...i did an episode where i wore blackface; the context is irrelevant because it's not ok to do blackface
column9: ever....i've been disgusted about it for a long time now & i'm sorry for anyone who was cut by it. i feel immense remorse & this is not some disingenuous bullshit...i was not caught. i mean this was on television it had to go through many filters which in itself is proof that we need to diversify our filters. that's not to say that people of color need to be in positions of power just to correct white people's worst instincts. it has to be my job to realize when i've contributed to a history of the degradation of an entire race of people....i'm sorry that i did this
column10: i wish that i could delete out of existence but i can't. i can only be changed by it & then make it right the best i can in anyway that i can...going forward.""

column1: 275562;instagram;2018-10-24 13:02:13;FALSE;"time for an instagram takeover! meet alexandra ""allie"" curtis @alliecurtisri. allie is speaking at the young women political leadership track at newpc on 11/16 about her efforts to bring young women into fields where women have been historically underrepresented. she's running our story for the next 24 hours. hop on over to check it out and then get your tickets to newpc. link in bio. 👏👏👏

more about allie: alexandra curtis is currently enlisted in the rhode island army national guard and works full time as a public affairs specialist. curtis is a graduate of syracuse university @syracuseu  and holds a master of public affairs from brown university @brownu and master of science in administration of justice and homeland security from @salveregina. at syracuse
column2: she served as student body president and earned distinction for her research in political science. after graduating
column3: she worked in congresswoman ileana ros-lehtinen’s  @roslehtinen washington
column4: dc office.​ she served as @missamericari 2015 and was named a quality of life award finalist at @missamerica 2016 for her platform “leading ladies: equipping young women with the skills to lead.” driven by her dedication to bring young women into fields where women have been historically underrepresented
column5: curtis gave a tedxtalk titled “leading ladies: why representation matters."" 👏👏👏

column1: 275572;instagram;2018-10-24 13:07:02;FALSE;"ending addiction requires ending child abuse and giving children the tools of meditation and therapy early in life to deal with the inevitable struggles they will encounter
most people remain in denial about the connection between child abuse and addiction because oftentimes the parents are unable to admit that they hit
column2: beat and verbally abused their children and prefer to blame a disease that can't be cured or or tested for. in my experience even while in treatment parents changed the past and suddenly become unable to recall the incidents the victims remember and this further confuses the situation. often times when this happens there is no place for reconciliation because there is no admission to the incidents so in their mind there is nothing to be sorry for.

column1: by continuing to use this approach the problem continues and no one is healed. hurt children grow up to be hurt adults... they turn towards drugs and alcohol to escape and sadly repeat the same cycle of abuse in their own lives
if you are abusing your children or are seeing children being abused by their families help the child or go to therapy yourself and ask for help.
don't ignore abuse because it is uncomfortable
don't watch other adults abuse children and say nothing. you are complicit in the abuse at that point
abuse as a child leads to lifelong problems in every part of life. addiction is rooted in pain

column1: circa 1995: a saturday meeting. a client office. the exec asst. to the chairman meets the new recruit of the pr consultancy firm to take her up to the directors' floor. he kisses her on the cheek just before the lift stops. she blanks out
column2: but collects herself and carries on with the meeting. when it's exit time
column5: like a thief... she tells no one. but she ensures she is never alone for a meeting again.

column1: ca. 1996: an asst ed tells the art dept. that the new trainee's name is sunaina when it's not. because he thinks she has pretty eyes... it takes her two months

column3: another trainee. she is shouted at for not choosing sexy enough photos for the entertainment page. one whole week
column4: he takes her to the photo library to show her 'good' photographs
column5: all the while running his finger lasciviously over the cleavage
column6: breasts and hips of actresses in the photos. .

column3: another trainee. he calls up her parents to stop her going on a trip with friends
column4: subtly warns them of consequences. because she is only 'his'.

column2: pre-vishakha guidelines: two of the above mentioned trainees leave
column3: the third talks to her ed. he tries his best to help by getting her transferred to another department
column4: as does another female asst ed.  but they are overruled because ""it will set bad precedent of transfers being granted on the whims and fancies of trainees."" she also

column1: ca. 2005: a younger colleague pulls out the scrunchie that holds her hair in a ponytail
column2: declaring that she looks prettier with open hair. .

column1: ca. 2011: the ed (city) at the newspaper where she freelances tells her he could help her with plum  assignments if only she were more 'friendly'. .
ca. 2015: different ed. different woman. scene: repeat of 2011.
we - of the above stories - are the lucky ones... our horrors were commonplace...

column1: 275628;instagram;2018-10-24 12:11:07;FALSE;"transparency: one of the hardest parts of the growing and healing process. my emotions have been everywhere lately. one minute i’m up one minute i want to hide under a rock. i’ve been so reluctant to share on my feed out of fear. thoughts of being judged kept crossing my mind. i’m done being quiet. i’m done being fearful. i’m  done allowing my sexual abuse affect my life.

my story in a nutshell is i was molested by a family member from the age of 8years to 16years old. i appeared to be the happiest child as i am today playful with a smile that shines even during trying times. but i suffered silently. there were many times i did not feel worthy of the life god blessed me with. there were many times i wanted help but my mouth was glued shut. there were many times i cried
column2: cry baby cries as a sign of help. there were times i felt hopeless.

column1: but like seriously i’m done dwelling on this. i’m tired of letting this affect me in a negative way. i’ve decided to seek help. i can only identify as the strong woman that i am. i am able to help others face the light during dark times. i’ve witnessed it. and it feels so good for others who have dealt with what i’ve gone through to be free and confine in me. it allows me to know i’m walking in truth.  the more i speak
column2: shine light and encourage others i become more liberated. i still suffer from ptsd and each day i’m learning with gods grace to take a day at a time.

column1: i’m asking everyone to please assist me with my healing reign project of providing clean water for people of liberia. as water is not as accessible as it is to you and i. could you imagine not having clean water to drink
column2: wash your body and cook? i honestly cannot.water impacts every aspect of life.  it would mean a lot to me if you could help donate. it’s my first healing reign project.

column1: god has graced me with a sash and crown. winning the @missliberiauspageant is so symbolic. it’s given me a platform beyond my reach. it’s god’s way of telling me to heal be a voice for the voiceless
it is my healing reign.  psalms 147:3
if you would like to donate link is in bio

275659;instagram;2018-10-24 11:01:10;FALSE;"i'm shaking things up sisters! this conversation has come up a lot with friends lately so i wanted to bring it here and gain some insight from you guys... ♡
it's about the image we have of ourselves vs the image we want others to see. are they one in the same? in a perfect world we'd like them to be right?... but if we're honest with ourselves

column2: it took a long time to see the discrepancies in myself and the myriad of 'faces' i'd try to encapsulate on a daily basis.
i'd actually feel like a chameleon
column3: shifting shape and changing my opinions
column4: values and even my laugh to suit the people i was around. i would leave social outings and analyse everything i said or did until i felt sick thinking i'd caused offence or said something that exposed the imperfect parts of who i was.

column1: i realised the energy i was putting into being someone others wanted
column2: left no energy for me to be who i inately felt i was. it was so messed up! and so i stopped.... i stopped apologizing for things that werent my fault
column3: i stopped changing my appearance to look less like me
column4: i stopped buying shit because it was on trend
column5: i stopped being everything to everyone. i just stopped.

column1: because guess what? i'm the most disorganized person i know
column3: i talk way too much for an ordinary person
column4: my curly hair drives me insane and fashion is not my forté (#kmart4life)
column5: but none of that's going to change!

column1: we are who we are and no matter the clothes we wear
column4: the colour we dye our hair
column5: the photos we put on instagram... we will always be that person. like it or not.

column1: so i choose to like the shit out of it!

column3: please take a moment to share your thoughts/experiences below 😘 i'd love to hear them

column1: it is about the image we have of ourselves vs the image we want others to see. are they one in the same? in a perfect world we'd like them to be right?... but if we're honest with ourselves
column2: they do not always match up 🙄
it took a long time to see the discrepancies in myself and the myriad of 'faces' i'd try to encapsulate on a daily basis.
i'd actually feel like a chameleon
column3: shifting shape and changing my opinions
column4: values and even my laugh to suit the people i was around. i would leave social outings and analyse everything i said or did until i felt sick thinking i'd caused offence or said something that exposed the imperfect parts of who i was.

column1: i realised the energy i was putting into being someone others wanted
column2: left no energy for me to be who i inately felt i was. it was so messed up! and so i stopped.... i stopped apologizing for things that werent my fault
column3: i stopped changing my appearance to look less like me
column4: i stopped buying shit because it was on trend
column5: i stopped being everything to everyone. i just stopped.

column1: because guess what? i am the most disorganized person i know
column3: i talk way too much for an ordinary person
column4: my curly hair drives me insane and fashion is not my forté (#kmart4life)
column5: but none of that's going to change!

column1: we are who we are and no matter the clothes we wear
column4: the colour we dye our hair
column5: the photos we put on instagram... we will always be that person. like it or not.

column1: ”unexpectedly falling pregnant with my daughter is the best thing that has ever happened to me. violet was a surprise
column3: she was the best surprise i’ve ever had. i’m scared and excited for her future. as a feminist
column4: i believe we still have a job as womxn to educate people of the earth to create equality for our future generations. i hope she’s feisty
column7: and kind. i hope she challenges the patriarchy and succeeds in what ever goal she has.  when violet was 8 weeks old
column8: i was diagnosed with post natal depression and anxiety. my super supportive fiancé recognised the symptoms and with his support and our fabulous nhs i got the help i needed to kicks it’s ass.

column1: i created a brand called tough mother @toughmotherclub to help share parents stories and views on post natal depression and anxiety. i still have episodes of depression and dips in my mental health but i have a great support system in my amazing friends and family. my daughter is the reason for everything i do. i try my hardest every day to be the best mother i can. even if some days my hardest is sitting on the sofa all day with her watching disney films and eating jaffa cakes.” 👩‍👧

column1: 275777;instagram;2018-10-24 09:54:11;FALSE;"have you ever said this to yourself? ""i just feel like i ruin everything i love because of my past""

i would. i'd say that all the time... i felt like i would destroy everything i loved... right when things started to get a little better with my boyfriend i would tear everything back down... have you ever done this?
this was the state of my life for years!
i would get closer with my boyfriend
column2: we'd go on dates to apple-bees (triple chocolate meltdown!)
column3: i'd open up a little bit
column4: and we'd start being happy again.

column2: there was always something inside me that kept saying i didn't deserve all this... and
column3: then i would proceed to pick fights with him...get mad a little things...and very effectively tear down everything i built.

column1: that was bad don't get me wrong!

column2: do you know what was worse?

column1: the guilt. the shame. and the blame.
i would break things down in my life
column2: and then go ahead and beat myself up for doing it.

column1: have you ever felt this way?

column2: if you have you're not alone... and it's not your fault!

column1: things completely changed when i realized this 1 thing... there was one day where this became crystal clear in my mind... i suddenly became aware of the separation inside of myself.
the separation of ""me""... my true self... and my hurt self

column2: but listen to this... i realized that when i was in a state of tearing everything down
column3: my hurt self was acting for me.

column1: my hurt self would take control of me and just ruin everything. i thought that this part of me was me... i thought it was the true me... which is why i blamed myself.
i thought that i was a horrible person... but
column2: what i didn't realize was that this was a very very hurt part of me acting for me.

column1: when i realized that i was able to comfort that part of myself. i showed it (myself) love
and when i was aware of when it started to take control
column2: i was able to calm it down
column4: and understand where it was coming from.

column1: that hurt part of me was trying to help me avoid more pain that i had in my past.

column1: 275815;instagram;2018-10-24 09:08:54;FALSE;"women are always portrayed as fragile and weak. but society doesn’t realize that our fragility comes from hiding our true selves. at any moment
column2: we can explode and destroy everything in our path with our power.

column1: that explosion can be untapped potential
column2: undiscovered talent and even undisclosed secrets of sorrow and humiliation
column3: of pain and suffering received at the hands of those sometimes trusted and revered
column4: sometimes too powerful and sometimes too corrupt to take on.

column2: undergoing something that scarred you wasn’t you being too weak or allowing someone else to exploit you.
don’t name and shame an innocent; it’s also important to remember not to shame those whose innocence is lost as they finally gather the courage
column3: summon the will to stand up for themselves.

column1: not everyone can slap back instantly
column2: not everyone can kick and fight back. it doesn’t make them weak or stupid or anything similarly insulting. it was a moment where they were overpowered by someone due to reasons we might not always know or understand. stand by and with if you can or sit down and stay quiet. judging is the easiest job in the world
column3: until you walk a mile in someone’s shoes.

column1: ✨it’s okay if you come from a poor background. it’s okay if you come from an incomplete and unstable family. it’s okay if if you are gay. it’s okay if you are a lesbian. it’s okay if you are black
column3: mixed etc. it’s okay if you have no experience in a job you have applied for. it’s okay if you are not as conservative as your family. it’s okay if no one else believes in you. it’s okay to be clueless on a topic. it’s okay if you didn’t go to school. it’s okay if you go to school later. it’s okay if all you know how to do is cook. it’s okay if you have a tooth gap. it’s okay if you have big lips. it’s okay if your nose is too sharp! it’s okay to be you and have your own story!✨

column1: خب کپشن خاصی نداشتم برای این عکس گفتم براتون یه کم از ترند یا همون جنبش me too بنویسم 📝
جالب بدونید چرا امسال جزو ترندها هست 👇🏻

گسترش سوءاستفاده جنسی از زنان در سیاست و سینما سبب شد تا دو ترند مهم در این باره در شبکه های اجتماعی رواج یابد. یکی هشتگ #me_too و دیگری هشتگ  #timesup که حتی نمادهایی از آن بر روی لباس سلبریتی های مرد و زن سینماگر جهان در رویدادهای سینمایی چند ماه اخیر نصب شد.
یکی از جاهایی که بیشتر سلبریتی ها این اعتراض رو رعایت کردند گلدن گلوب بود که بیشترشان لباس مشکی پوشیدند.
ولی در ترند پاییز و زمستان 2019 /2018 تاثیر اعتراض me too (که گفتم جنبش اعتراضی به #تجاوز علیه زنان در سرتاسر جهان )  بر روی طراحی ها بسیار زیاد است.
و این تاثیر در طراحی های کاملا زنانه مشهود است.
این ترند شامل لباسهایی میشود که زنانگی در آن کمتر دیده میشود مثل لباسهای اور سایز و ...

column1: 275972;instagram;2018-10-24 06:29:49;FALSE;"🗞рафаиля фейзиева приговорили к 15 годам лишения свободы за убийство супруги. мужчина убил ее из ревности
column3: однако оправдывался “честью”. “я всегда буду держать голову высоко поднятой. я принесу всю свою семью и детей в жертву своей чести”

column1: по данным оон жертвами “убийств чести” по всему миру ежегодно становятся более 5000 женщин. чаще всего они происходят в религиозных обществах
column2: но бывают случаи и в официально светских государствах
как журналисты сразу нескольких изданий опубликовали статьи о том
column3: как влиятельнейший кинопродюссер харви вайнштейн десятки лет домогался
column5: угрожал и преследовал актрис и сотрудниц своей кинокомпании.

column1: спустя год благодаря движению против домогательств более 200 влиятельных американцев потеряли свои рабочие места. для сравнения
column2: в год до возникновения #metoo за домогательства на рабочем месте были уволены лишь 30 человек.

column1: раньше нанимать женщину было рискованным делом
column2: потому что она могла оставить работу из-за беременности или своих уже рожденных детей. теперь же
column5: что мужчина-начальник может принести больше рисков компании.

column1: так место уволенного за домогательства редактора vox media локкарта стила была назначена мелисса белл
column2: вместо главы студии amazon роя прайса — дженнифер салке
column3: а главной героиней сериала “карточный домик” вместо кевина спейси стала робин райт. всего женщины заняли главные позиции вместо мужчин в 54 случаях (другие мужчины заняли освободившиеся должности в 70 случаях).

column1: 📇двух женщин оштрафовали за ношение никаба еще в 2012 году
column2: но жалоба поступила в оон лишь в 2016 году. наконец
column3: в 2018 году комиссия оон признала нарушением прав человека то
column4: что женщин оштрафовали за их одежду. запрет на ношение никаба во франции действует с 2010 года.

column1: после решения комиссии франция в течение полугода должна выплатить пострадавшим женщинам компенсацию и принять меры
column2: чтобы не нарушать прав человека в будущем.
